DEK wrap recipes (OpenSSL)
===========================

Each file ``dek-wrap-recipe-NN.conf`` (NN = 01‚Äì99) defines how ``dek.encrypted``
is produced: cipher, PBKDF2 iteration count, minimum OpenSSL version, and
header layout. Fixed inputs for openssl self-tests live in
``../dek-wrap-test-vectors.bash``. The numeric id is stored in the 16-byte util
header on ``dek.encrypted`` (bytes 10‚Äì11, uint16 big-endian).

Override the directory with ``KEYRING_DEK_WRAP_RECIPE_DIR`` (default: this
directory next to ``lib.bash``).

Recipe 01 is the only recipe today; future ids can add new parameter sets while
old ciphertext remains readable via the embedded recipe id.

OpenSSL binary path is pinned with ``KEYRING_OPENSSL_BIN`` (default:
``/usr/bin/openssl``).
